cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DL 

This paper is about keyphrase extraction from scientific articles, which is a task related to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also uses neural networks, which are a popular tool in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DL (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, keyphrase extraction is a task that involves text analysis and classification, which are topics covered by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning and Statistics).
